chordpro:
{title: O Little Town of Bethlehem}
{subtitle: Phillips Brooks, 1868 — "St. Louis" tune by Lewis Redner}
{key: F}
{time: 4/4}
{tempo: 76}
{comment: Pair with ああベツレヘムよ (Japanese, 讃美歌 第二篇 1910).}

{start_of_verse: 1}
[F]O little [C]town of [Dm]Bethle[Bb]hem
[F]How still we [C]see thee [F]lie:
[F]Above thy [C]deep and [Dm]dreamless [Bb]sleep
[F]The silent [C]stars go [F]by;
[Dm]Yet in thy [Am]dark streets [Bb]shineth
[F]The Ever[C]lasting [F]Light;
[F]The hopes and [C]fears of [Dm]all the [Bb]years
[F]Are met in [C]thee to[F]night.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
[F]For Christ is [C]born of [Dm]Mar[Bb]y
[F]And gathered [C]all a[F]bove
[F]While mortals [C]sleep, the [Dm]angels [Bb]keep
[F]Their watch of [C]wondering [F]love.
[Dm]O morning [Am]stars, to[Bb]gether
[F]Proclaim the [C]holy [F]birth!
[F]And praises [C]sing to [Dm]God the [Bb]King
[F]And peace to [C]men on [F]earth.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
[F]How silent[C]ly, how [Dm]silent[Bb]ly
[F]The wondrous [C]gift is [F]giv'n;
[F]So God im[C]parts to [Dm]human [Bb]hearts
[F]The blessing [C]of His [F]heaven;
[Dm]No ear may [Am]hear His [Bb]coming
[F]But in this [C]world of [F]sin,
[F]Where meek souls [C]will re[Dm]ceive Him [Bb]still
[F]The dear Christ [C]enters [F]in.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
[F]O Holy [C]Child of [Dm]Bethle[Bb]hem!
[F]Descend to [C]us, we [F]pray
[F]Cast out our [C]sin, and [Dm]enter [Bb]in
[F]Be born in [C]us to[F]day;
[Dm]We hear the [Am]Christmas [Bb]angels
[F]The great glad [C]tidings [F]tell;
[F]O come to [C]us, a[Dm]bide with [Bb]us
[F]Our Lord Em[C]manu[F]el!
{end_of_verse}
